quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to output "PHP is awesome" to the screen.
[!raw!]
<?php
$arr[0] = 'PHP';
$arr[1] = 'awesome';
$arr[2] = ' is ';

echo "$arr[{0}] $arr[{1}] $arr[{2}]" ;
?>

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Numeric Arrays[/h1]

You can have integers, strings, and other data types together in one array.
[b]Example:[/b] [code format="swift" codeId="473"]<?php
$myArray[0] = "John";
$myArray[1] = "<strong>PHP</strong>";
$myArray[2] = 21;

echo "$myArray[0] is $myArray[2] and knows $myArray[1]";

// Outputs "John is 21 and knows PHP"
?>[/code]
